devdoc.details: Smart contract for conducting a voting process using blockchain technology

addProposal(string).details: Adds a new proposal to the proposals array.

params._desc: A string representing the proposal's description.

addVoter(address).details: Registers a new voter by adding their address to the list of voters.

params._addr: The address of the voter to register.

endVotingSession().details: End the voting session and update the workflow status to `VotingSessionEnded`.

getOneProposal(uint256).details: Returns a single proposal from the proposalsArray based on its ID.

params._id: uint ID of the proposal to retrieve.

returns._0: Proposal memory The proposal object containing all of its details.

getVoter(address).details: Returns the voter information for a given address.

returns._0: The voter's information including registration status, vote status, and voted proposal ID.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setVote(uint256).details: Allows a registered voter to vote for a proposal with a given ID.

params._id: The ID of the proposal to vote for.

startProposalsRegistering().details: Allows the owner to start the proposals registration process

startVotingSession().details: Start the voting session, only the contract owner can call this function

tallyVotes().details: Tally the votes and determine the winning proposal.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

devdoc.title: Voting

addProposal(string).notice: Requirements:- The workflow status must be set to ProposalsRegistrationStarted.- The proposal description cannot be an empty string.- Only registered voters can add a proposal.Emit a ProposalRegistered event.

addVoter(address).notice: Requirements:- The workflow status must be "RegisteringVoters".- The voter must not already be registered.Emit a VoterRegistered event.

endProposalsRegistering().notice: Only the owner can call this functionThe workflow status must be "ProposalsRegistrationStarted"Once the function is called, the workflow status will be changed to "ProposalsRegistrationEnded"Emits a "WorkflowStatusChange" event with the previous status "ProposalsRegistrationStarted" and the new status "ProposalsRegistrationEnded"

endVotingSession().notice: This function can only be called by the contract owner.Requires that the workflow status is currently `VotingSessionStarted`.Emits a `WorkflowStatusChange` event with the previous and current workflow status.

setVote(uint256).notice: Requirements:- Voting session must have started.- The voter must not have voted before.- The proposal ID must exist.Emit a Voted event.

startProposalsRegistering().notice: This function can only be called when the workflow status is set to RegisteringVotersThe function initializes the workflow status to ProposalsRegistrationStartedThe function also creates a GENESIS proposal with id 0Emits a WorkflowStatusChange event with the old and new workflow status

startVotingSession().notice: The workflow status must be `ProposalsRegistrationEnded` to start the voting sessionEmit a `WorkflowStatusChange` event with `ProposalsRegistrationEnded` and `VotingSessionStarted` as parameters

tallyVotes().notice: Can only be called by the owner of the contract.The current status of the contract must be VotingSessionEnded.Emits a WorkflowStatusChange event with the old and new statuses.

userdoc.notice: This contract allows voters to register, submit proposals, and vote on proposalsThe voting process has multiple stages that are controlled by the contract ownerVoters can only vote once and can only vote on proposals that have been registeredThe winning proposal is the one with the highest number of votesOnly the contract owner can tally the votes and determine the winning proposal
